The inspiration for today's video was an outfit I wore when I took my wife out last weekend. I got so many compliments from men and women at the party for wearing a simple pair of black loafers, tailored black dress pants, and a black polo from Collars & Co. I heard about the company from Shark Tank, where Mark Ruben invested a million dollars. Collars & Co. solved the problem of floppy polo collars with different options ranging from standard to button-down to dress-shirt. Other features are buttery soft-and-smooth fabric and sleeves that don't have that annoying band around them.
As you know, not all polo shirts are created equal. Some are stylish and sexy, whereas others make you look like a little boy or a boring and basic dad. You can elevate the aesthetic if you rock a polo properly. I will review some of the most significant polo-wearing mistakes most men make.

Disheveled and sloppy collars. Most polos have wacky and crazy collars that don't look crisp and clean. They make men look like little boys rather than polished men. Elevate your polo style with a not-too-big or floppy collar. You can either iron it or upgrade the quality of your polo.

Clashing aesthetic. The look is mismatched if you wear a casual polo under a suit, especially if your collar is bad and basic. Make sure the polo underneath matches aesthetically.

Striped and bright fabric. No man looks good in a striped polo shirt. I'm not saying all patterns are bad, as a smaller tight pattern is incredible. But stripes make men appear shorter, wider, and like little boys. Also, bright colors are not sexy. They are loud and make men look like they're wearing circus tents. Go with more subdued and muted colors.

Visible undershirt. Being able to see an undershirt makes men look sloppy. With the placket open, the polo can make men's faces look chiseled and refined without the undershirt. If you're going to wear an undershirt, make sure it's a deep v.

Skin tight. Cotton polos that have been thrown in the dryer shrink. You can see dudes rocking cropped polos all the time. Make sure your polo is not cropped or too tight. Look for it to hit the mid-crotch area. If you lift your arms up and your happy trail is visible, it's too short. Also, ensure it's not covering your crotch, or your body proportions will appear messed up and sloppy.

Do you button your polo all the way? This look may be trendy, but having the placket open draws the eye down, making a man's face look more angular and chiseled.

Is your polo collar wacky and balcony? This is a mistake.

Are your polo sleeves short? A band on the sleeve will cinch the arm and make the sleeve look too high -- a douchey look.

Can you see your mid-drift if you raise your arms while wearing a polo? You don't want to look like Britney Spears. You will get zero sex.

Is your polo striped? This is not a good look.

00:00 Polo Shirt Introduction

A polo shirt is one of the most versatile shirts any man can own. Chances are, you already own an array of these shirts, and every Classic wardrobe will benefit from the presence of at least one polo to serve as a casual sport shirt that is especially well-suited for warmer weather. 

01:04 History Of The Polo Shirt

As the name implies, the history of the polo shirt is closely linked to the history of the game of polo, although the modern polo shirt as we recognize it today looks very different from its ancient antecedent. 

03:10 The Polo Shirt Today

From their origins on the polo fields, polo shirts have come to dominate menswear. Few other garments are seen on middle managers and suburban dads as often as they are glimpsed on celebrities and music stars. 

03:57 Polo Shirt Hallmarks: Materials
04:38 Knits
05:10 Sleeves & Cuffs
06:12 Collars & Plackets
07:39 Buttons & Buttonholes
08:14 Other Details

When selecting a polo shirt, take advantage of the following list of quality hallmarks to make a selection that falls within your desired price point while also leveraging the full potential of this versatile and functional garment.

08:46 How to Style a Polo Shirt

Now that you know how to find the best polo shirt, we will share with you tips and tricks to achieve the best possible look in your polo.

11:42 How to Buy a Polo Shirt

When it comes to a summer wardrobe, it‚Äôs not a bad idea to have a selection of polo shirts. I usually recommend at least having a navy and a white polo shirt but it‚Äôs wise to include other colors as well. Follow these guides to get tips for finding and buying the perfect polo shirt.

12:08 Outfit Rundown

Kyle is wearing a tan polo shirt from Ralph Lauren, a famous purveyor of polo shirts. He has opted to wear it untucked, and selected a shirt with an appropriately short hem. To emphasize this more casual styling, Kyle's trousers are dark-washed jeans, which harmonize well with his dark brown, pebbled oxfords. The entire look is given a subtle pop of color thanks to his midnight blue and burgundy Fort Belvedere socks.

The polo shirt is a men‚Äôs style essential. Every single one of you should have some of these in your wardrobe because you can dress them up and dress them down. They are so versatile! Today, I want to make sure you‚Äôre wearing your polo properly and go over a few polo wearing rules so you look like a sexy stud as opposed to a big humongous dork. I‚Äôm also going to show you a few of my favorite ways to rock a badass polo this spring and summer.
Polo Wearing Rules
Don‚Äôt wear big bold bright patterns or colors. These will make you look youthful when you actually want to look as sexy as possible. Go with a solid color such as blacks, greens, grays, and blues.
The fit matters! Don‚Äôt wear a polo that is too tight or one that is too big and baggy. The right fit is the most important aspect of wearing any piece of clothing, including polos. You will find some polos are square and boxy. I like Cuts Clothing polos because they are a bit snug in the chest and arms, and the body is tailored and tapered without being too tight.
Pay attention to your collar and sleeves. With a standard polo, these both will get sloppy and messed-up eventually. Look for a crisp, clean, and small collar that sits up. Invest in a higher quality polo that will fit better and not get super stretched out in the sleeves. The sleeve length should not cover your bicep and tricep, which will make your arms look super skinny.
The placket is important. Polos make you look sexy because of the natural fall or opening of the placket when you leave it unbuttoned. You‚Äôre drawing the eye down very similar to a v-neck shirt or a Henley. It‚Äôs creating a visual illusion. Don‚Äôt button it all the way up. Also, you should also not see a visible undershirt that is a no-go.
To tuck or not to tuck ‚Äî it‚Äôs up to you. With polos you can tuck them in or you can leave them untucked or even do a partial tuck. The length should not be too long, hitting midway down your crotch.
Here‚Äôs how to rock a polo even better
The dressiest polo look. I absolutely love this outfit. You can dress down your suit with a polo in the summer and spring. I‚Äôm rocking it with a charcoal suit. Take off the jacket, and your polo is now paired with your slacks. We‚Äôre simple clean minimal loafers with no socks, and you‚Äôre absolutely killing it.
The second look is a bit more casual and sporty. I start with the white simple minimal sneaker with Cuts Clothing joggers and a simple, sexy, gray polo. It‚Äôs sporty and fun and fresh.
Crush it with double monks plus medium wash jeans, and a  beautiful green polo. It‚Äôs casual and subdued, and it‚Äôs a great date outfit.
Chi chi chi chinos are your light-weight warm weather pants. Match the green polo from the previous outfit with these chinos and some simple casual loafers with no show socks.
Check out my favorite date night outfits. Dark-washed non-distressed jeans, black dress shoes or loafers, and the perfect black polo is one my all time favorite ensembles.

00:00 Ralph Lauren Polo Shirts Introduction 

The Ralph Lauren Polo shirt is a staple of prep style and has become near ubiquitous as a piece in many of our closets. The iconic pony logo is recognized across the globe as a symbol of luxury and it‚Äôs usually the first thing many people think of when they imagine a polo shirt.

00:45 The History of Ralph Lauren

Ralph Lauren was founded by Ralph Lifshitz in 1967. He named the company ‚ÄúRalph Lauren‚Äù because he thought it‚Äôd be more marketable than with his true last name. 

The Polo brand only grew in prestige after being featured prominently in 1974‚Äôs The Great Gatsby and later Annie Hall. The brand then gained global recognition as they expanded outside of the US starting in the 80s. The added global attention brought them in direct competition with LaCoste, who was the one who arguably first invented the original shirt style and Sunspel, who helped to popularize the pique cotton that polo shirts were made of.

03:25 Ralph Lauren Polos in Contemporary Menswear

The popularity of Ralph Lauren Polos has remained a consistent mainstay in mainstream fashion, though they have ebbed and flowed throughout pop culture. The ‚Äúpony‚Äù so prominently featured in Polo‚Äôs clothing got its initial appeal as a status symbol and remains a cornerstone of the brand to this day.

04:53 Ralph Lauren Polo Product Range

One of Ralph Lauren‚Äôs most defining decisions was to break the brand down into several different lines. The actual Polo line has a large variety of offerings outside of their classic short sleeve mesh polo at $110 retail. This includes long-sleeved polos, polos with pockets and some interesting fabrics like Terry Cloth.

08:30 Ralph Lauren Polo Construction

On the Ralph Lauren site, the iconic mesh shirt is simply listed as being made of ‚Äúcotton‚Äù. Sure, there‚Äôs cotton in there, but without a listed amount it‚Äôs impossible to be certain it‚Äôs 100% cotton. It also has a ribbed collar, two-button placket, and ribbed armbands which are classic design features. We also don‚Äôt get any information on if the buttons are plastic, shell, or MOP. When you look at the stitching around the buttonholes, you can see that they‚Äôre stitched and then cut.

With all of these construction methods in mind, it looks like the classic polo shirt is definitely a mass-manufactured item.

09:47 Assessing Ralph Lauren Polo Shirts

13:09 Is It Worth It?

If you‚Äôre a fan of the Ralph Lauren brand, and like the history and prestige behind it, the Polo line Polo shirts are perhaps one of the most iconic garments they make. The Polo Line shirt certainly can be a dependable, good-looking product that is a perfectly valid option as an addition to your wardrobe. Ultimately making the Ralph Lauren Polo line Polo shirts worth it, on average.

Polos are extremely versatile. You can wear them with shorts, jeans, chinos or even wool trousers. In fact, you can even tuck them in and wear them under a blazer or sport coat.

The problem is, many men don't understand how polo shirts should fit, and they end up wearing ill-fitting polos that make them look shorter and fatter than they really are.

This is especially true for short men because it's hard to find a polo shirt that flatters men 5'8" and under (at least from major brands, without any alterations).

When it comes to how polo shirts should fit, there are three things to pay attention to:

#1: Overall length
#2: Body width (tight vs. baggy)
#3: Sleeve length and width

Remember: a polo shirt that fits is very flattering and versatile. But when your polo doesn't fit well, it's not a good look, especially if you're a man of modest height.

Questions? Ask me in the comments below!

00:00 Lacoste Polo Shirt Introduction

The famous Lacoste crocodile is one of the most iconic logos in sporty menswear, and it‚Äôs typically associated with polo shirts, as well as luxury, in that regard.

01:05 History of Lacoste

Today, Lacoste is a big player in the polo shirt market, valued at around 2.3 billion US dollars. Even though they sell a bunch of different things, front and center is definitely their polo shirt.

Most Lacoste polos are made from a piqu√© knit, but they also have jersey knits and a t-shirt style material. They‚Äôre almost made out of 100% cotton, and there are some blends. If you want to learn more about the best polo shirt materials, our guide has you covered.

Lacoste Polo Shirt Review
We look at seven different Lacoste polo shirts, and all of them were 100% cotton, which is fairly the standard for the brand, at least in the US. 
03:58 Material & Quality
06:58 Colorfastness and Color Range
07:20 Collars
08:10 Buttons and Buttonholes
09:35 Logo Detail
10:24 Construction
11:36 Shirt Pricing
12:35 Different Models
13:22 How do Lacoste Polos Fit?

In our experience, Lacoste's original polo, overall, quite small for American size. That being said, there are differences between the sizes. In terms of length, the classic is longer than the regular, which is longer than the slim.

While the Paris polo comes in a classic fit and a regular fit. It‚Äôs different visually because it has a hidden front placket, so you don‚Äôt see the buttons, and the collar is definitely smaller. Also, the famous crocodile logo is tone-on-tone, so it‚Äôs a little more subdued. And, personally, I‚Äôd rather have no logos on my chest, so I‚Äôd rather wear the Paris polo than their original one.

16:36 Other Styles Lacoste Offers
18:43 Pros of a Lacoste Polo Shirt
19:28 Cons of a Lacoste Polo Shirt

20:35 Is the Lacoste Polo Shirt Worth It?
First of all, figure out what you want out of your polo shirt. If you just want something to wear while doing your garden work or run around the house, maybe spending the extra money on the Lacoste branding is not justified. If you wear polo shirts regularly during the summer and enjoy wearing them, it can be a good contender.

The big questions, then, are: Does the polo fit you, or does it puddle weirdly? Or does it have weird wrinkles, and do you like the fit and the style, as well as the fabric they offer?

Do you want a polo shirt in just the basic colors such as navy or, maybe, gray? Then, you can go with other brands. But, if you want those special, unusual colors, I think Lacoste is really good.

When it comes to brands, here at Gentleman‚Äôs Gazette, we, generally, don‚Äôt put too much value or emphasis on that, and we rather look at the quality and the value, which is the quality to price ratio.

00:00 Sunspel Polo Shirts & T-Shirts Introduction

Even here at the Gentleman‚Äôs Gazette, we can‚Äôt deny the appeal of a quality T-Shirt or Polo Shirt.  But in today‚Äôs ever casual world, it can be a genuine challenge to find an alternative to a dress shirt that is of equal quality and standing for a lover of classic style. So it‚Äôs with this in mind that we look towards Sunspel, a brand offering a clean, cool take on how traditional casualwear can be relevant for the 21st Century.

01:00 History of Sunspel

Thomas Hill founded Sunspel in 1860 when he opened a hosiery and underwear factory. Instead of manufacturing man-tights for local vigilantes, Hill‚Äôs aim was to create beautiful, everyday clothing from the world‚Äôs finest fabrics. Ten years later, in 1900, the company starts importing the world‚Äôs rarest and finest cotton, Sea Island cotton from the Caribbean. 

Continuing to innovate, the year 1914 saw the introduction of Cellular cotton.  Sunspel factory also relocates to the nearby town of Long Eaton. The year 2005 marks the sale of the company from then 81-year-old Peter Hill to Nicholas Brooke and Dominic Hazlehurst.

As the company changed and grew into the 21st century, costume designer, Lindy Hemming, saw a unique opportunity to utilize the brand‚Äôs rich British history to outfit James Bond in 2006‚Äôs Casino Royale.

04:23 Sunspel Today

05:36 T-Shirt or Undershirt?

That being said, there is a difference between a T-Shirt and an undershirt which is important because Sunspel offers both. So although they might look similar at first glance, there are a few characteristics of both varieties that set them apart.

07:10 T-Shirts

 Sunspel does offer a few different varieties of T-Shirt models often being made in a different fabric or featuring different details such as a long sleeve or a V neck but the style we‚Äôre looking at today is their iconic, classic T-shirt.

09:40 Polo Shirts

By far the most popular style of polo shirt in the range is the Riviera model, which is crafted from Sunspel‚Äôs unique Q75 warp knit cotton, a two-button placket at the collar, a patch pocket on the left breast, and flat, stitched seams. Meanwhile, the Sea island cotton polo shirts feature a three-button placket at the collar, a flat front with no additional pocket, and ribbed seams. 

Sunspel also offers a traditional pique cotton polo shirt, which is closer in style to the Sea Island cotton polos.

12:45 Are Sunspel Shirts Worth It?

In our experience, Sunspel‚Äôs everyday, Classic cotton jersey T-shirts and Riviera polo shirts are of excellent quality, wash and wear well, and most importantly, fit into our classic wardrobes effortlessly.

Welcome to our full polyester polo shirt embroidery tutorial! In this video, we'll guide you through the process of embroidering a polo shirt made of 100% polyester fabric. Whether you're a beginner or an experienced embroiderer, this tutorial is designed to help you achieve professional results.

Here's what you'll learn in this video:
Choosing the right embroidery design for polyester fabric
Preparing your embroidery machine and materials
Hooping the polyester polo shirt correctly
Adjusting the settings for polyester fabric
Stitching out the embroidery design
Finishing touches and tips for a clean result

Embroidering on polyester can be tricky due to the delicate nature of the fabric, but with the right techniques and guidance, you can create stunning embroidered designs on your polo shirts.
